<tr><td colspan="2" class="MsgR3">
<span class="MsgBodyText"><b>Originally posted by:</b> thomas.x.hughes.jpmorgan.com<br />
<br />
Hi,<br />
<br />
Trying to get to grips with the databinding framework. One thing I want to <br />
do is bind to a list of objects to a table. A new row should be added to <br />
the table when the list is added to and a row deleted when an item in the <br />
list deleted. Fairly standard stuff.<br />
<br />
I'm using the standard PropertyChangeListener mechanism to make my bean <br />
properties observable. e.g. :<br />
<br />
class TransientMarketService <br />
{<br />
  public static final String PROP_MARKETS = &quot;markets&quot;;<br />
  private List&lt;Market&gt; markets;	<br />
<br />
  public TransientMarketService()<br />
  {<br />
    markets = new ArrayList&lt;Market&gt;();<br />
  }<br />
<br />
  public void create(Market market)<br />
  {<br />
    markets.add(market);<br />
    fireIndexedPropertyChange(PROP_MARKETS, markets.size(), null, market);<br />
  }<br />
<br />
  public void delete(Market market)<br />
  {<br />
    int index = markets.indexOf(market);<br />
    fireIndexedPropertyChange(PROP_MARKETS, index, market, null);<br />
  }<br />
}<br />
<br />
To use the ObservableListContentProvider I need to provide an <br />
IObservableList. However my list is not one of those and I don't <br />
particularly want to make it so - it seems odd to use <br />
PropertyChangeListeners for non-collection properties and  <br />
IObservableCollections for collection properties.<br />
<br />
Questions are :<br />
  * Is it recommended to use IObservableLists in the domain.<br />
  * If so, why so? Were indexed property change events not workable?<br />
  * Is there or is it possible to create an adapter between a collection <br />
attribute firing indexed property events and an IObservableCollection.<br />
<br />
thanks, Tom Hughes</span>


<div class="SmallText"><p class="fr"><a href="index.php?t=report&amp;msg_id=315061&amp;" rel="nofollow">Report message to a moderator</a></p></div>
