<tr><td colspan="2" class="MsgR3">
<span class="MsgBodyText">Tom Hughes wrote:<br />
&gt; 2. The inconsistency is very possibly in my head...<br />
&gt; What I am looking for is an example of an observable domain object which <br />
&gt; includes both simple and say List attributes. For example a Person <br />
&gt; object with a name and a List&lt;Person&gt; of relations.<br />
&gt; What are the recommended idioms?<br />
<br />
It sounds like you don't have an existing technology that you're using <br />
to implement your model correct?  And in technology I mean you're <br />
determining if you should be using the JavaBean spec or something else. <br />
  In most cases that I've encountered the model technology is <br />
predetermined or determined by a factor other than UI technology.  So <br />
EMF might already be employed or the model objects might have to be <br />
designed in a particular way to work with hibernate or some other <br />
persistance mechanism.  If looking for patterns employed when <br />
developing UIs I normally look to Martin Fowler[2].  Presentation <br />
Model[1] is a common pattern that seems to drive the design of similar <br />
toolkits[3] and works well with the concept of observables and bindings. <br />
  What is appropriate is going to be a combination of preexisting model <br />
needs and also your own opinion.  If you don't have preexisting needs <br />
then I would look at making my domain model as UI agnostic as possible <br />
so that I don't push UI dependencies into my domain model.<br />
<br />
-brad<br />
<br />
[1] <a href="http://www.martinfowler.com/eaaDev/PresentationModel.html" target="_blank">http://www.martinfowler.com/eaaDev/PresentationModel.html</a><br />
[2] <a href="http://www.martinfowler.com/eaaDev/uiArchs.html" target="_blank">http://www.martinfowler.com/eaaDev/uiArchs.html</a><br />
[3] <a href="https://binding.dev.java.net/" target="_blank">https://binding.dev.java.net/</a></span>


<div class="SmallText"><p class="fr"><a href="index.php?t=report&amp;msg_id=315202&amp;" rel="nofollow">Report message to a moderator</a></p></div>
