&gt;&gt; Ed Merks schrieb:<br />
&gt;&gt;&gt; Tom,<br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;<br />
&gt;&gt;&gt; I feel like a salesman jumping into this thread, but I should point <br />
&gt;&gt;&gt; out that EMF generates models that fully support notification.  Even <br />
&gt;&gt;&gt; multi-valued properties are surfaced as lists that are editable and <br />
&gt;&gt;&gt; will notify.  The notification support is so complete that you can <br />
&gt;&gt;&gt; attach a ChangeRecorder to an model instance that records all <br />
&gt;&gt;&gt; notifications and can convert them to a ChangeDescription, which can <br />
&gt;&gt;&gt; them be applied to undo all the changes (and reapplied to redo the <br />
&gt;&gt;&gt; changes).  It's a very handy way to support a dialog with cancel or <br />
&gt;&gt;&gt; to implement undo/redo.  It's also an interesting way to interact <br />
&gt;&gt;&gt; with a server where you might want to send back only a description of <br />
&gt;&gt;&gt; the changes you've made; a change description is also a model <br />
&gt;&gt;&gt; instance and can be serialized to and from XML just like any other <br />
&gt;&gt;&gt; EMF model instance.  You might find that EMF will generate much of <br />
&gt;&gt;&gt; your application<br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;<br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;     The Eclipse Modeling Framework Overview<br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;     <br />
&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;<a href="http://dev.eclipse.org/viewcvs/indextools.cgi/*checkout*/org.eclipse.emf/doc/org.eclipse.emf.doc/references/overview/EMF.html" target="_blank"> http://dev.eclipse.org/viewcvs/indextools.cgi/*checkout*/org .eclipse.emf/doc/org.eclipse.emf.doc/references/overview/EMF .html</a>&gt; <br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;<br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;     The EMF Edit Framework Overview<br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;     <br />
&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;<a href="http://dev.eclipse.org/viewcvs/indextools.cgi/*checkout*/org.eclipse.emf/doc/org.eclipse.emf.doc/references/overview/EMF.Edit.html" target="_blank"> http://dev.eclipse.org/viewcvs/indextools.cgi/*checkout*/org .eclipse.emf/doc/org.eclipse.emf.doc/references/overview/EMF .Edit.html</a>&gt; <br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;<br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;     Tutorial: Generating an EMF Model using XML Schema<br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;     <br />
&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;<a href="http://dev.eclipse.org/viewcvs/indextools.cgi/*checkout*/org.eclipse.emf/doc/org.eclipse.emf.doc/tutorials/xlibmod/xlibmod.html" target="_blank"> http://dev.eclipse.org/viewcvs/indextools.cgi/*checkout*/org .eclipse.emf/doc/org.eclipse.emf.doc/tutorials/xlibmod/xlibm od.html</a>&gt; <br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;<br />
